@node Displaying startup time
@section Displaying startup time

@findex use-package-extras-display-startup-time
The function @code{use-package-extras-display-startup-time} calculates and displays how long Emacs took to initialize and how many garbage collections occurred during startup. It computes the elapsed time from @code{before-init-time} to @code{after-init-time} and reads the @code{gcs-done} variable, then formats the result into a message like ``Emacs loaded in 0.52 seconds with 5 garbage collections.''

This function is typically added to @code{emacs-startup-hook} so the information appears in the echo area once initialization is complete. It provides a quick way to monitor whether configuration changes are affecting startup performance.

